{ An excellent move. Now Black's king becomes quite vulnerable. } 15... Bxd5
16. Qf5
{ White regains the piece with interest. After  16...g6  17.Qxd5  ,  White has the bishop pair and he can start a kingside attack with h2-h4. Additionally, Black was forced to weaken the dark squares around his king. }
