{ White occupies the open a-file and it also helps that the square a7 is under our control. }
15... h6 16. Red1 Nb6 17. dxe5 dxe5 18. Bc5
{ We seize control over the dark-squares, and in particular, d6 becomes vulnerable. Black cannot fight for control over the d-file as well. }
18... Be6 19. Bxe7 Qxe7 20. Qd6 Re8 21. Qxe7 Rexe7 22. Ne1
{ the white Knight is coming to d3, where it will control the squares e5 and c5 fully. }
22... Bxb3 23. cxb3
{ White controls both open files and he intends to play Nd3-c5, putting solid pressure on the enemy Queenside. Sulit,F -Bishop,W ICCF email 2019. }
